GateDocument.TextWithNodes: >From cmbm @ qu . vq . ho Tue Mar 24 07 : 20 EST 1998 To : cmbm @ nwdh . bq . ka Subject : jaiio Content- Type : text Content- Length : 3932 X-L ines : 105 Status : RO Argentine Workshop on Database Systems BDATOS 98 Buenos Aires , September 3 - 4 , 1998 FINAL CALL FOR PAPERS The Argentine Workshop on Database Systems is a scientific meeting that will be sponsored by SADIO ( the Argentine Society on Operations Research ) . The Workshop will be held in conjunction with the IX Latin Iberoamerican Conference on Operations Research . The goal of the workshop is to provide a forum for dissemination of theoretical and practical results of research in the area of database systems . The workshop will host technical sessions , one guest tutorial and panels . Authors are encouraged to submit papers describing relevant , original and unpublished research related ( but not restricted to ) the following topics : - Active , deductive , temporal and spatial databases - Cooperative , multimedia and hyperedia databases - Database theory and algorithms - DBMS implementation aspects - Data modelling and database design techniques - Database support for advanced applications - Data mining , workflow and data warehouses - Knowledge discovery in databases PAPER SUBMISSION - EXTENDED ABSTRACTS ONLY - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Authors should send 4 copies of extended abstracts , limited to 2500 words ( 6 double spaced pages ) , preferrably in English . Papers should be sent to the Symposium 's Chair ( no Fax submissions are allowed ) : Claudia Bauzer Medeiros - BDATOS 98 IC - UNICAMP - CP 6176 13081 - 970 Campinas SP - Brazil Phone : ( + 5519 ) 239 - 3115 e-mail : cmbm @ eelsj . wbk . vg Submission of an extended abstract is assumed to imply that at least one of the authors will register for the conference and thus present the paper . The criteria for paper analysis are originality , relevance , technical soundness and clarity of presentation . PUBLICATION - - - - - - - - - - - Accepted papers will appear in the Proceedings published by the Argentina Computer Science Society , in CD-ROM . Authors are encouraged to submit papers written in English . Papers in Spanish are also accepted . A selection of complete papers ( chosen from all papers submitted to the Conference ) will be published in a special issue of the SADIO Electronic Journal ( in English ) . ELECTRONIC SUBMISSIONS - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Electronic submissions are encouraged . Basic electronic formats are the following : a ) For papers without figures , tables , special symbols - send the TEXT file ( ascii ) without formatting characters or symbols , leaving blank lines between paragraphs b ) For all other papers - send an HTML file ( ascii ) with figures in www-readable format or - send a PDF file which can be read by Adobe AcrobatReader 3 The subject of the message containing the paper must be "BDATOS 98". IMPORTANT DATES - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - . Deadline for extended abstract submission : May 5 th , 1998 ( firm deadline ) . Notification of acceptance : July 1 st , 1998 . Camera-ready papers due in Buenos Aires : July 17 , 1998 .
